 <p>Cartumandua Spiritslammer
"Phat Loot, No Work" - The Druid Motto</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugaramebonhands.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garam Ebonhands</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#CC9900>(2/15/01 11:04:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Intentions board: DATA</span><hr size=1> Nicely put together Cart.  In this case I could agree, however I think this just opens the pandora's box for placing other reservations in the game.<br>
<br>
Where does that lead?  Well eventually someone from &quot;a smaller guild&quot; (refering to relative power, not relative numbers in the guild), will want to put something on reservation.  The &quot;bigger guilds&quot; (again power), will shoot this down.  Then begins the endless cycle of arguements about board corruption, and higher players controlling the board.  Thus, leading to a &quot;new generation&quot; of higher level players believing in FFA against a waining older generation who hold tight to the current system.<br>
<br>
Sound far fetched?  It's already happening.<br>
<br>
There are currently problems with FG's reservations because they are easy to do with few numbers.  Trakanon doesn't suffer the same problem because not any 6 people can go in and kill him.  I think Phingel would fall into the same loop as FG's because there is a significant portion of the population that can take 6 people in and do Phingel in 15 minutes.<br>
<br>
Yes, I realize that not everyone can go in with six people and the same arguement was used when FG's came up about 5 months ago.  However, I believe a majority of the high level players &quot;could&quot; kill him with 6 people if they so choose.  Merry Band proved it along time ago, I'm sure SR only takes a group, and Darkguard proved it about a month ago.  As to the arguements saying it's a good way for guilds to learn raiding tactics and organization, I say we already have FG's for that, as well as Naggy and Vox.<br>
<br>
People only get angry when they believe something is theirs, by reserving Phingel you are making that spawn theirs and that leads to territorial disputes.<br>
<br>
Garam Ebonhands<br>
Vicar of Darkguard<br>
